{"key":"post-13361344","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>13361344</id>\n<content>Don't use a spoon to remove mycelium from a grain master.&amp;nbsp; Bang the jar against a tire or block of wood to loosen the individual kernels, and then simply pour and twist to allow the grains to pour into the receiving jars.&amp;nbsp; Using a spoon adds another vector of contamination, and also takes longer, increasing exposure.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Glove boxes need not be sterile.&amp;nbsp; Wash it with soap and water and for best results, use it while still wet.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>13361354</next>\n<prev>13361320</prev>\n<first>13361042</first>\n<last>13361985</last>\n<when>1287589922</when>\n<utime>10/20/10 06:52 PM</utime>\n</post>"}